23/01/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The new EU police mission Proxima needs access to information gathered by all government institutions to work efficiently, according to mission head Bart d'Hooge. 
Speaking Thursday (22 January), he acknowledged that obtaining the information would not be easy. 
He added that Proxima has been well received so far, and described local support as vital to the success of the mission. 
Its mandate expires at the end of the year.
In other news Thursday, Macedonia and Greece signed a memorandum of understanding, envisioning the opening of offices for consular, economic and commercial affairs in Bitola and Thessaloniki. 
The move is expected to boost diplomatic and economic relations. 
(Dnevnik - 23/01/04; MIA - 22/01/04)
